title: Hard to find in a box store
description: I used to purchase this from Wal-Mart before the pandemic, then all of a sudden it became impossible to find in any auto parts store.  After locating it on Amazon, I found the price went up $18.  Overall it's an excellent product but not sure how long I will keep using this brand especially since the price hike.
date: Reviewed in the United States on June 2, 2023

title: Good Cost effective oil
description:
The price is what i liked most for an engine oil formulated fir v twin motors with a wet clutch.
Just as good as the higher priced synthetics.
I change my oil often fir added protection of my engine.

title: Works fine
description: Decent oil depending on the price. Performs much like any other oil I have used. Most oils manufactured today are of good quality meeting established ratings JASO MA2 etc. with only subtle differences the average user really won't see. I ride my bikes like an average user so even conventional oils work fine be it with a slight reduction in longevity/shift feel.

title: Perfect Amount for my V-Star 1300 Tourer
description: Lot easier than pouring it in a quart at a time and close enough to capacity to just pour in the full gallon.  In the past, I've gone 8-9K on a synth oil change.  Expect to do the same this time.  Time will tell.
